org.nasdanika.codegen.ecore.web.ui.model

Interface ETypedElementConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CDOObject, CDOWithID, EModelElementConfiguration, ENamedElementConfiguration, EObject, Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EAttributeConfiguration, EReferenceConfiguration, EStructuralFeatureConfiguration
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EAttributeConfigurationImpl, EReferenceConfigurationImpl, EStructuralFeatureConfigurationImpl, ETypedElementConfigurationImpl

    public interface ETypedElementConfiguration
extends ENamedElementConfiguration

    A representation of the model object ‘ETyped Element Configuration’.

    The following features are supported:

    • Visible
    • Editable
    • Disabled
    • Location
    • Category
    • Control
    • Control Configuration
    • Input Type
    • Form Input Group
    • Placeholder
    See Also:
    ModelPackage.getETypedElementConfiguration()

    • Method Detail

      • getVisible

        String getVisible()

        Returns the value of the ‘Visible’ attribute. Defines whether the feature is visible in the object view. The value can be one of the following:

        • Blank string or true boolean literal - the feature is visible.
        • false boolean literal - the feature is hidden.
        • JXPath expression. If this expression evaluates to true (compared with Boolean.TRUE), then the feature is visible.
        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Visible’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setVisible(String), ModelPackage.getETypedElementConfiguration_Visible()

      • getEditable

        String getEditable()

        Returns the value of the ‘Editable’ attribute. Defines whether the feature is editabe if it is already visible. The value can be one of the following:

        • Blank string - the feature is editable if it is not an item (isItem() returns false)
        • true boolean literal - the feature is editable
        • false boolean literal - the feature is not editable.
        • JXPath expression. If this expression evaluates to true (compared with Boolean.TRUE), then the feature is editable.
        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Editable’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setEditable(String), ModelPackage.getETypedElementConfiguration_Editable()

      • getDisabled

        String getDisabled()

        Returns the value of the ‘Disabled’ attribute. Defines whether an editable feature is disabled, i.e. it shall be displayed in the edit form, but the edit control shall be disabled.

        • false boolean literal or empty string - the feature is enabled (default).* true boolean literal - the feature is disabled.
        • JXPath expression. If this expression evaluates to true (compared with Boolean.TRUE), then the feature is disabled.
        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Disabled’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setDisabled(String), ModelPackage.getETypedElementConfiguration_Disabled()

        TypedElementLocation getLocation()

        Returns the value of the ‘Location’ attribute. The literals are from the enumeration TypedElementLocation. Format is used for rendering and parsing date and number feature values. SimpleDateFormat for dates, DecimalFormat for numbers.

        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Location’ attribute.

      • getCategory

        String getCategory()

        Returns the value of the ‘Category’ attribute. Feature category. Categories are displayed as panels in the view and the left panel, and field sets in edit forms.

        Features with a common prefix are auto-categorized if not explicitly categorized. E.g. features databaseUser and databasePassword will be auto-categorized under the category Database with labels User and Password respectively.

        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Category’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setCategory(String), ModelPackage.getETypedElementConfiguration_Category()

      • isFormInputGroup

        boolean isFormInputGroup()

        Returns the value of the ‘Form Input Group’ attribute. Set it to true to force rendering of the form control in a FormInputGroup instead of FormGroup or to false to force the opposite. If this annotation is not present then inputs with either icon (rendered on the left) or help icon (rendered on the right) are rendered as form input groups.

        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Form Input Group’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setFormInputGroup(boolean), ModelPackage.getETypedElementConfiguration_FormInputGroup()

      • getPlaceholder

        String getPlaceholder()

        Returns the value of the ‘Placeholder’ attribute. XPath expression evaluating to the placeholder value for features. Placeholder value is an implicit application-specific value, different from the default value. For example, in hierarchical structures children may implicitly inherit parent feature value, unless it is explicitly set (overridden) in the child.

        In the absence of feature value (null or blank string for strings) placeholder values are displayed in the view in a small Well.

        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Placeholder’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setPlaceholder(String), ModelPackage.getETypedElementConfiguration_Placeholder()
